# Validation & testing (Templ registry)

Validate **bricks**, **utils**, and **examples** ‚Äî not only `ui/` and `components/`.

## Routine checks

From repository root:

```bash
bun run generate
bash .validate/scripts/validate-spec.sh --with-tests
bun run lint:ui8px
bun run validate:aria
go test ./...
```

Or combined:

```bash
bun run verify
```

### Pipeline

| Step | Command | Scope |
|------|---------|--------|
| Variant invariants | `variantcheck` (in `verify`) | every `*.variants.json` |
| Block grammar | `blockonce` (in `verify`) | one `<Block>` per TSX/Templ file |
| Codegen | `bun run generate` | `examples/ui/blocks/*/page_gen.go`, `*_templ.go` |
| Spec contract | `validate-spec.sh` | `ui/**/*.spec.md`, `components/**/*.spec.md`, `utils/*.spec.md`, `examples/**/*.spec.md` |
| Blockgen freshness | `blockgen --check` (in validate-spec.sh) | generated `page_gen.go` matches spec/data/variants |
| Variant maps | `validate-spec` | `*Variants` / `*.variants.json` ‚Üî `api.enum` |
| React test target | `validate-spec` | `targets.react.test` file must exist when declared |
| ui8px | `bun run lint:ui8px` | `ui/`, `components/`, `utils/`, `examples/` |
| ARIA manifest | `bun run validate:aria` | `examples/` markup vs `examples/web/static/js/manifest.json` |
| Go tests | `go test ./...` | brick tests, `examples/*_render_test.go` |

## ui8px scope

Policy root: **[`.ui8px/policy/`](../../.ui8px/policy/)**.

Lint paths (see root `package.json`):

- `ui/` ‚Äî primitive bricks and `Class` strings
- `components/` ‚Äî composite bricks
- `utils/` ‚Äî shared variant base strings and recipes
- `examples/` ‚Äî preview pages, demo compositions, block scaffolds
- `examples/web/static/css/input.css` ‚Äî `@source` entry (when listed)

After `.templ`, `Class` strings, `*.variants.json`, or CSS `@source` edits: **`bun run lint:ui8px`**.

## Spec validation

```bash
bash .validate/scripts/validate-spec.sh --with-tests
```

Checks include:

- required front matter on brick specs;
- `showcase[].id` ‚Üî `## Example {id}` fences;
- `allow-list-source` ‚Üî `utils/tags.go`, `utils/utils.go`, or `*.variants.json`;
- no empty-string variant keys and valid defaults;
- `targets.react.test` existence when declared;
- `components.json` alias expectations.

Example block specs: `examples/ui/blocks/home/home.spec.md`, `examples/ui/blocks/dashboard/dashboard.spec.md`.

## Go render tests

Add or extend `*_render_test.go` when markup contracts matter:

- `components/components_render_test.go` ‚Äî composite bricks
- `examples/page_render_test.go` ‚Äî preview document shell
- `examples/ui/blocks/*/page_render_test.go` ‚Äî demo scaffolds

Assert class strings, roles, and opt-in `data-ui8kit` hooks ‚Äî not browser behavior.

## Examples preview (manual)

`examples/` is a Bun workspace member of the repo root; dependencies are
installed once via `bun install` at the repo root, not inside `examples/`.

```bash
bun run dev:templ
```

Rebuild client bundle after hook or `@ui8kit/aria` changes:

```bash
cd examples && bun run build:js
```

